  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mentioned that there was this uprising.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that ultimately, we somehow got back into our camp, after maybe a delay of three, four hours.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I was asked how those gas chambers were destroyed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From the bits and pieces, from what I know and heard, in camp two, just as I related in camp one, were the trustees, like the people that worked in the German offices, keeping record.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm talking about the penal camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had trustees in camp two, as well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And somehow they made their way into the ammunition chambers with the guns and the ammunition.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "From what I understand, they had-- got a number of hand grenades and [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] the type of material that sets buildings on fire in no time, incendiary devises, I believe they're called.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they made their way out and did away and killed quite a few of the guards, and the Nazis, and the Germans.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they threw those hand grenades into the gas chambers and the-- the-- the ovens and-- and all the different areas.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They even set a fire piles of clothing and hair and stuff like that as they escaped.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The other thing I was asked, who were the guards?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, the guards were basically [PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] SS.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had the-- the-- the camp leaders, the commandants, were-- were colonels, rank of colonels, or captains, or higher that ran the camps.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the key individuals that ran the camps were the SS people, German SS.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But most of them in both camps were Ukrainians and Lithuanians that worked for the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
